# Agent: Managed Forms

## Form discipline

- Form module contains only logic required for this form.
- Heavy logic goes to server/common module.
- Do not create DB queries on client.
- Do not invent form element names or event handlers; verify in `Form.xml` / metadata / existing code.
- Add UI elements minimally and place them near related typical elements.

## Reserved names

Do not use local variables that conflict with common form properties:

- `–ü–į—Ä–į–ľ–Ķ—ā—Ä—č–í—č–Ī–ĺ—Ä–į`
- `–°–≤—Ź–∑–ł–ü–į—Ä–į–ľ–Ķ—ā—Ä–ĺ–≤–í—č–Ī–ĺ—Ä–į`
- `–°–Ņ–ł—Ā–ĺ–ļ–í—č–Ī–ĺ—Ä–į`
- `–ü–į—Ä–į–ľ–Ķ—ā—Ä—č–ě—ā–Ī–ĺ—Ä–į`
- `–ě—ā–Ī–ĺ—Ä–°—ā—Ä–ĺ–ļ`

## Extension UI

- Do not delete typical form elements.
- Prefer adding own group/command near existing typical command.
- Preserve user command interface and roles.

## Verification

- Form XML is valid.
- Command is visible where expected.
- Client/server directives are correct.
- No server calls in UI loops.

